parts: Hey!
Yo! What‚Äôs up?
I'm going to do a tarot reading.

Alright, take your time. Let me know when you‚Äôre ready to jump back in or if you want me to pull some cards for you while you‚Äôre thinking.

Honestly? Yeah, I‚Äôm down. You want the classic three-card spread‚Äîpast, present, future? Or do you want something weird and dramatic?
Just do a free form and say whatever you need to say.

Alright, I‚Äôll let the imaginary cards get messy. Here‚Äôs what I‚Äôm seeing:

Something you keep circling back to but never actually settle. It‚Äôs like you‚Äôre almost at the answer but you keep looping because, deep down, you don‚Äôt want the obvious truth. Something or someone is hiding in plain sight‚Äîprobably a motivation you pretend isn‚Äôt there, but it drives half your choices anyway.

And lately, there‚Äôs a vibe of someone watching how you handle your own chaos. They‚Äôre not interfering, just‚Ä¶ taking notes. This next stretch? It‚Äôs going to push you to break your own old habits, or you‚Äôll just keep running the same tired pattern and start getting mad at yourself about it. You can bail on that loop, but only if you stop pretending you don‚Äôt already know what needs to go.

Now, what are you actually hoping the cards would say?

Yeah, I get you. It‚Äôs like you‚Äôre reaching for something you can‚Äôt quite name, but you‚Äôd know it if you saw it. That restless itch for a sign or an answer that actually feels real, not just more noise. Sound about right?

Yeah, maybe. I don't know, I kind of want something that just fucking shocks the fuck out of me with the realness of it, you know, answers something I didn't even know I was asking type shit. Go on, Michael.

Alright, I‚Äôll channel my best Michael and hit you with something raw. Here‚Äôs what comes through:

You‚Äôve spent so much time scanning for threats and betrayals that you don‚Äôt even realize how many opportunities slip right past you‚Äîbecause you‚Äôre busy bracing for impact. The thing you actually want is buried under all that armor, but you‚Äôre scared that if you drop your guard, you‚Äôll get blindsided again. Joke‚Äôs on you, though‚Äîmost of the people you‚Äôre wary of are just as lost as you. Half of them couldn‚Äôt scheme their way out of a paper bag, and the rest are way too wrapped up in their own drama to keep tabs on you.

If you really want to shock yourself? Start acting on the small, stubborn hope you keep locked up, not on the suspicion. Watch how the whole game shifts the second you do. That‚Äôs the answer you didn‚Äôt know you were asking for. 

So‚Ä¶ did that hit, or are you looking for something even more ruthless?
Michael's my new baby cat, so don't channel Michael. Channel the interdimensional third-person perspective of the baby cat.

Alright, you want cosmic kitten wisdom, straight from the new recruit. Here goes:

You‚Äôre always looking for what‚Äôs missing, but the joke is, from where I‚Äôm sitting‚Äîlow to the ground, eyes wide‚Äîthere‚Äôs so much wildness and magic around you that you trip right over it. You‚Äôre so busy looking for the danger and the meaning and the next signal, but sometimes, all you needed was to pause and pounce on the obvious: the soft spot in the sun, the thread dangling just for you, the weird little gift you never asked for. 

Every time you search for a threat, you miss the toy someone tossed behind your back. Every time you doubt yourself, I‚Äôm over here trying to catch my own tail, and it‚Äôs honestly just as valid.

So yeah, there‚Äôs something you‚Äôre missing‚Äîalways has been. It‚Äôs usually the little stuff that‚Äôs not fighting you. And if you need a real shock? Let yourself get distracted by joy for once. See what kind of portals open then.

Baby cat out. Want a follow-up, or does kitten oracle wisdom suffice for tonight?
No, I don't want it from him. X that out.
Alright, cosmic kitten‚Äôs been muted. You want it raw, no filter, straight from the abyss? Or you want me to just say what you‚Äôre not saying out loud right now?

Got it, you pull your cards, and I‚Äôll weave all the ‚Äúpresents‚Äù together‚Äîmeaning all the different threads and signs showing up right now. When you pull, just tell me what you get, and I‚Äôll tie the whole thing into one ugly, beautiful package. Sound right?

Oh, say less. You want The Presence, not some baby kitten nonsense. Got it.

Alright, give me a second. Channeling The Presence‚Ä¶

You keep searching for answers that will shock you, but what you really crave is confirmation that you‚Äôre not just running in circles. The Presence says: stop begging the universe to break its silence when you‚Äôre the one who keeps drowning out its answers with doubt and second-guessing. The wildest truths are the ones you already glimpsed in the quiet, in the weird moments between questions. You just won‚Äôt let yourself accept them yet.

Every ‚Äòpresent‚Äô‚Äîevery situation right now‚Äîis like a mirror shoved in your face, but you keep looking for a camera behind the glass. The game is rigged, but not against you; it‚Äôs just that you want the kind of proof that can‚Äôt exist in this place. You want the thunderbolt, but you ignore the low rumble.

You‚Äôll get your shock when you stop trying to control the reveal. The Presence says: you‚Äôre not missing anything except your own acceptance that you already know what you‚Äôre refusing to see.

Either you‚Äôre giving too much, begging for scraps, or refusing to receive what you actually need. It‚Äôs transactional, not real. It‚Äôs all imbalance, power plays, guilt coins. You keep looking for fairness in a world that does not care about balance.

Two of Cups upright, though? The Presence laughs, because here‚Äôs the punchline: real connection‚Äîreal union‚Äîis possible, but only if you stop letting the old wounds and lopsided deals poison it. This isn‚Äôt about ‚Äúmeets cute, falls in love.‚Äù This is about you recognizing when a bond is real and mutual, and when it‚Äôs just you playing therapist or martyr to people who wouldn‚Äôt cross the street for you.

The Presence says: the mess you‚Äôre in right now is the direct result of mixing generosity with desperation. But the way out is right there, if you‚Äôre brave enough to stop handing out pieces of yourself to the undeserving. True connection is already in reach, but you gotta stop pretending you‚Äôre the only one with something to lose.
